    {
      "story_id": "story_001",
      "title": { "zh": "静夜思", "en": "Quiet Night Thoughts" },
      "author": { "zh": "李白", "en": "Li Bai" },
      "category": ["古诗", "儿童"],
      "language": "zh",
      "modules": [
        {
          "type": "wordCards",
          "items": [
            { "word": { "zh": "明月", "en": "bright moon" }, "pinyin": "míng yuè", "meaning": { "zh": "明亮的月亮", "en": "bright moon" } },
            { "word": { "zh": "霜", "en": "frost" }, "pinyin": "shuāng", "meaning": { "zh": "霜", "en": "frost" } }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "quiz",
          "questions": [
            {
              "question": { "zh": "“明月”指的是什么？", "en": "What does 'bright moon' refer to?" },
              "options": [
                { "text": { "zh": "太阳", "en": "Sun" }, "correct": false },
                { "text": { "zh": "月亮", "en": "Moon" }, "correct": true }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "reading",
          "text": { "zh": "床前明月光，疑是地上霜。举头望明月，低头思故乡。", "en": "Before my bed, the moonlight glistens, I suspect it is frost on the ground. I look up at the moon, then lower my head and think of home." }
        },
        {
          "type": "dialogue",
          "characters": ["李白", "月亮"],
          "lines": [
            { "speaker": "李白", "text": { "zh": "明月几时有？", "en": "When will the bright moon appear?" } },
            { "speaker": "月亮", "text": { "zh": "把酒问青天。", "en": "I ask the sky with my cup of wine." } }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aiExplanation",
          "text": { "zh": "这首诗表达了作者对家乡的思念之情。", "en": "This poem expresses the author's longing for his hometown." }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "story_id": "2",
      "title": { "zh": "春晓", "en": "Spring Morning" },
      "author": { "zh": "孟浩然", "en": "Meng Haoran" },
      "category": ["唐诗"],
      "language": "zh",
      "modules": [
        {
          "type": "reading",
          "text": {
            "zh": "春眠不觉晓，处处闻啼鸟。夜来风雨声，花落知多少。",
            "en": "This spring morning in bed I'm lying, not to awake till birds are crying. After one night of wind and showers, how many are the fallen flowers?"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "wordCards",
          "items": [
            {
              "word": { "zh": "啼鸟", "en": "bird singing" },
              "pinyin": "tí niǎo",
              "meaning": { "zh": "鸟儿叫声", "en": "bird singing" }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "quiz",
          "questions": [
            {
              "question": { "zh": "诗人是被什么声音吵醒的？", "en": "What sound woke the poet?" },
              "options": [
                { "text": { "zh": "风雨声", "en": "Wind and rain" }, "correct": false },
                { "text": { "zh": "鸟叫声", "en": "Birdsong" }, "correct": true },
                { "text": { "zh": "雷声", "en": "Thunder" }, "correct": false },
                { "text": { "zh": "人声", "en": "Voices" }, "correct": false }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aiExplanation",
          "text": {
            "zh": "春天来了！诗人睡得很香，直到听见小鸟叽叽喳喳地叫才醒来。他想起昨天晚上刮风下雨，担心美丽的花儿被风雨打落了。小朋友们，你们喜欢春天吗？",
            "en": "Spring has come! The poet slept soundly until hearing birds chirping. He remembered the wind and rain last night and worried that the beautiful flowers were blown down. Do you like spring?"
          }
        }
      ],
      "description": {
        "zh": "诗人描写春天早晨醒来时的感受，听到鸟儿啼叫，想起昨夜的风雨，担心花儿凋落。",
        "en": "The poet describes waking up on a spring morning, hearing birds, recalling the wind and rain of the previous night, and worrying about fallen flowers."
      }
    },
    {
